idual species as a percentage of the number of", "bbox": [45.5, 711.8, 693.4, 723.4]}, {"text": "isolates from each subject identiﬁed using species-speciﬁc primer sets.", "bbox": [45.5, 726.9, 359.0, 738.5]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0157516.t004", "bbox": [45.5, 749.8, 186.2, 761.2]}, {"text": "complete rpoB gene sequences. In addition, the distribution and frequency of five species of", "bbox": [252.5, 785.5, 707.4, 799.4]}, {"text": "oral Veillonella in tongue biofilms of healthy adults were analyzed by PCR with these specific-", "bbox": [252.5, 801.9, 719.4, 815.8]}, {"text": "primer sets as performed in our previous study [12]. Furthermore, species-specific primer pairs", "bbox": [252.5, 818.4, 727.0, 832.3]}, {"text": "for V. tobetsuensis were designed using the sequence of the dnaK gene in the region displaying", "bbox": [252.5, 834.7, 721.3, 848.7]}, {"text": "a high degree of polymorphism (positions 424–1048) [48]. In addition, the distribution and", "bbox": [252.5, 851.1, 708.2, 865.1]}, {"text": "frequency of six species of oral Veillonella in the periodontal pockets were recently clarified by", "bbox": [252.5, 867.5, 721.1, 881.5]}, {"text": "PCR using these primer sets and those of our previous study [21]. Thus, our previous study", "bbox": [252.5, 884.0, 706.6, 897.9]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | DOI:10.1371/journal.pone.0157516 June 21, 2016 11 / 16", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}